---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

---

<Layout title="Katrinah.io | Home">
	<main>
		<h1>Hi! I'm <span class="text-gradient">Katrina</span>.</h1>
		<p><i>I'm a Design Systems & Product Designer, also a former Front End Developer. I love working at the intersection of design and code. 💜</i></p>
		<p class="intro">
			Here, I'll be documenting my process of redesigning this personal site and maybe coding in public. <strong>Insert cringe 😬!</strong><br />I intend to start sharing my knowledge and things I learn about designing and coding design systems! 🥳
		</p>
		<div>
			<p>To Do:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><s>Say goodbye 👋🏾 to Gatsby &amp; Gatsby Cloud</s></li>
				<li><s>Set up Astro and deploy to Netlify</s></li>
				<li>Create the design system... because why not!</li>
				<li>Design the website</li>
				<li>Design & write case studies</li>
				<li>Write and publish blog posts</li>
				<li>Coninuously upload/publish</li>
				<li>Maybe even <a href="https://twitter.com/TrinaBHu">tweet</a> about it too!</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
		<div>
			<p>9/15/23 - It's been pretty busy over here so this endeavor has been on pause for a bit. I did manage to upgrade to Astro 3.0 this week. I've also started a couple of online classes around design, design systems and <a href="https://astro.build/" target="_blank">Astro</a> of course!</p>
		</div>
		<div>
			You can follow these updates on <a href="https://github.com/katrinah">Github</a>!
		</div>

	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	main {
		margin: auto;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		max-width: 60ch;
	}
	h1 {
		font-size: 3rem;
		font-weight: 800;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.text-gradient {
		background-image: var(--accent-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-size: 400%;
		background-position: 0%;
	}
	.intro {
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 1rem 0;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--accent), 25%);
		background-color: white;
		padding: 1rem;
		border-radius: 0.4rem;
	}
</style>
